Class RadarResults

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<ObjectStatus>, java.util.Collection<ObjectStatus>, java.util.List<ObjectStatus>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public class RadarResults
extends java.util.ArrayList<ObjectStatus>
    Represents the results of a radar sweep.

    Each radar sweep will return a collection of ObjectStatus objects representing the objects in range of the radar sweep. If a level 1, 2, or 4 sweep was performed, these ObjectStatuses will not be fully populated. Attempting to access data that was not determined by the radar sweep will result in a zero-equivalent value.

    Since:
    0.1
    See Also:
    RadarCommand, Serialized Form

      • getByType

        public java.util.List<ObjectStatus> getByType(java.lang.String type)
        Gets the details read by this radar sweep for all objects of the given type. Case-insensitive comparison is used for type names.

        Could be Ship, Planet, BlackHole, Star, Nebula, Asteroid, Torpedo, Bauble, Bubble, or Outpost.

        Parameters:
        type - the type of object for which to return results
        Returns:
        a list of radar details for all objects of the given type (may be empty)
